During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Karine Jean-Pierre discussed various topics, including the popularity of President Biden's American Families Plan, the trip to Georgia, police reform, the ban on menthol cigarettes, the meeting with former President Jimmy Carter, the withdrawal of U.S. troops from Afghanistan, and the issue of voting rights. She also addressed questions about the Vice President's role in leading on broadband, the status of U.S. journalist Austin Tice who is being held in Syria, and the President's stance on Confederate flags and statues.